{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. As such, we often need to deprecate certain APIs","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in favor of newer ones. We recommend people update their code as quickly as possible to the newest","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"APIs, and this article contains some tips for doing so.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Sending test store actions","anchor":"Sending-test-store-actions","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Version 1.4 of the library introduced the ability to receive test store actions using case key path","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"syntax, massively simplifying how one asserts on actions received in a test:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["-store.receive(.child(.presented(.response(.success(\"Hello\")))))","+store.receive(\\.child.response.success)"],"syntax":"diff","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"While version 1.6 of the library introduced the ability to assert against the payload of a received"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"action:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["store.receive(\\.child.presented.success, \"Hello\")"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Version 1.9 introduces similar affordances for "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"sending","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" actions to test stores via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TestStore\/send(_:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)-8877x"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestStore\/send(_:_:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)"},{"type":"text","text":". These methods can significantly simplify"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"integration-style tests that send deeply-nested actions to child features, and provide symmetry to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"how actions are received:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["-store.send(.path(.element(id: 0, action: .destination(.presented(.record(.startButtonTapped))))))","+store.send(\\.path[id: 0].destination.record.startButtonTapped)"," store.receive(\\.path[id: 0].destination.record.timerTick)"],"syntax":"diff","type":"codeListing"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Case key paths offer specialized syntax for many different action types.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentationAction"},{"type":"text","text":"’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"presented"},{"type":"text","text":" case can be collapsed:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["-store.send(.destination(.presented(.tap)))","+store.send(\\.destination.tap)"],"syntax":"diff"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/IdentifiedAction"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackAction"},{"type":"text","text":" can be subscripted into:"}]},{"syntax":"diff","code":["-store.send(.path(.element(id: 0, action: .tap)))","+store.send(\\.path[id: 0].tap)"],"type":"codeListing"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"And ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/